Tea output in India, the worldâ€™s
largest grower after China, dropped 9 percent in August after a
pest attack damaged crop in the biggest growing regions.  Production was 122.7 million kilograms, compared with 134.4
million kilograms a year earlier, the state-run Tea Board said
on its website. Output in the January-August period fell 1.7
percent to 584.9 million kilograms, it said.  Exports dropped 21 percent to 16.8 million kilograms in
August from 21.4 million kilograms a year earlier, it said.
Shipments in the eight months ended Aug. 31 climbed 8 percent to
124.1 million kilograms from 114.7 million  a year earlier, the
